blqs-class.summary: The ByteLengthQueuingStrategy interface of the the Streams API provides a built-in byte length queuing strategy that can be used when constructing streams.
blqs-class.title: ByteLengthQueuingStrategy

blqs-constructor.summary: The ByteLengthQueuingStrategy() constructor creates and returns a ByteLengthQueuingStrategy() object instance.
blqs-constructor.title: ByteLengthQueuingStrategy.ByteLengthQueuingStrategy()

blqs-size.summary: The size() method of the ByteLengthQueueingStrategy interface returns the given chunk’s byteLength property.
blqs-size.title: ByteLengthQueuingStrategy.size()

byob-reader-cancel.summary: The cancel() method of the ReadableStreamBYOBReader interface cancels the stream, signaling a loss of interest in the stream by a consumer. The supplied reason argument will be given to the underlying source, which may or may not use it.
byob-reader-cancel.title: ReadableStreamBYOBReader.cancel()

byob-reader-class.summary: The ReadableStreamDefaultReader interface of the Streams API represents a BYOB ("bring your own buffer") reader that can be used to read stream data supplied by the developer (e.g. a custom ReadableStream.ReadableStream() constructor).
byob-reader-class.title: ReadableStreamBYOBReader

byob-reader-closed.summary: The closed getter property of the ReadableStreamBYOBReader interface returns a promise that fulfills if the stream becomes closed or the reader's lock is released, or rejects if the stream errors.
byob-reader-closed.title: ReadableStreamBYOBReader.closed

byob-reader-constructor.summary: The ReadableStreamBYOBReader() constructor creates and returns a ReadableStreamBYOBReader() object instance.
byob-reader-constructor.title: ReadableStreamBYOBReader.ReadableStreamBYOBReader()

byob-reader-read.summary: The read() method of the ReadableStreamBYOBReader interface returns a promise providing access to the next chunk in the byte stream's internal queue.
byob-reader-read.title: ReadableStreamBYOBReader.read()

byob-reader-release-lock.summary: The releaseLock() method of the ReadableStreamBYOBReader interface releases the reader's lock on the stream. After the lock is released, the reader is no longer active.
byob-reader-release-lock.title: ReadableStreamBYOBReader.releaseLock()

cqs-class.summary: The CountQueuingStrategy interface of the the Streams API provides a built-in byte length queuing strategy that can be used when constructing streams.
cqs-class.title: CountQueuingStrategy

cqs-constructor.summary: The CountQueuingStrategy() constructor creates and returns a CountQueuingStrategy() object instance.
cqs-constructor.title: CountQueuingStrategy.CountQueuingStrategy()

cqs-size.summary: The size() method of the CountQueuingStrategy interface always returns 1, so that the total queue size is a count of the number of chunks in the queue.
cqs-size.title: CountQueuingStrategy.size()

default-reader-cancel.summary: The cancel() method of the ReadableStreamDefaultReader interface cancels the stream, signaling a loss of interest in the stream by a consumer. The supplied reason argument will be given to the underlying source, which may or may not use it.
default-reader-cancel.title: ReadableStreamDefaultReader.cancel()

default-reader-class.summary: The ReadableStreamDefaultReader interface of the Streams API represents a default reader that can be used to read stream data supplied from a network (e.g. a fetch request).
default-reader-class.title: ReadableStreamDefaultReader

default-reader-closed.summary: The closed getter property of the ReadableStream interface returns a promise that fulfills if the stream becomes closed or the reader's lock is released, or rejects if the stream errors.
default-reader-closed.title: ReadableStreamDefaultReader.closed

default-reader-constructor.summary: The ReadableStreamDefaultReader() constructor creates and returns a ReadableStreamDefaultReader() object instance.
default-reader-constructor.title: ReadableStreamDefaultReader.ReadableStreamDefaultReader()

default-reader-read.summary: The read() method of the ReadableStreamDefaultReader interface returns a promise providing access to the next chunk in the stream's internal queue.
default-reader-read.title: ReadableStreamDefaultReader.read()

default-reader-release-lock.summary: The releaseLock() method of the ReadableStreamDefaultReader interface releases the reader's lock on the stream.
default-reader-release-lock.title: ReadableStreamDefaultReader.releaseLock()

default-reader-release-lock.summary: The releaseLock() method of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface releases the writer's lock on the corresponding stream. After the lock is released, the writer is no longer active. If the associated stream is errored when the lock is released, the writer will appear errored in the same way from now on; otherwise, the writer will appear closed.
default-reader-release-lock.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.releaseLock()

default-writer-abort.summary: The abort() method of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface aborts the stream, signaling that the producer can no longer successfully write to the stream and it is to be immediately moved to an error state, with any queued writes discarded.
default-writer-abort.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.abort()

default-writer-class.summary: The WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface of the the Streams API is the object returned by WritableStream.getWriter() and once created locks the  writer to the WritableStream ensuring that no other streams can write to the underlying sink.
default-writer-class.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter

default-writer-close.summary: The close() method of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface closes the associated writable stream.
default-writer-close.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.close()

default-writer-closed.summary: The closed getter property of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface returns a promise that fulfills if the stream becomes closed or the writer's lock is released, or rejects if the stream errors.
default-writer-closed.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.closed

default-writer-constructor.summary: The WritableStreamDefaultWriter() constructor creates a new WritableStreamDefaultWriter object instance.
default-writer-constructor.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.WritableStreamDefaultWriter()

default-writer-desiredSize.summary: The desiredSize getter property of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface returns the desired size required to fill the stream's internal queue.
default-writer-desiredSize.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.desiredSize

default-writer-ready.summary: The ready getter property of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface returns a Promise that resolves when the desired size of the stream's internal queue transitions from non-positive to positive, signaling that it is no longer applying backpressure.
default-writer-ready.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.ready

default-writer-write.summary: The write() property of the WritableStreamDefaultWriter interface writes a passed chunk of data to a WritableStream and its underlying sink, then returns a Promise that resolves to indicate the success or failure of the write operation.
default-writer-write.title: WritableStreamDefaultWriter.write()

rbs-controller-byob-request.summary: The byobRequest getter property of the ReadableByteStreamController interface returns the current BYOB pull request.
rbs-controller-byob-request.title: ReadableByteStreamController.byobRequest

rbs-controller-class.summary: The ReadableByteStreamController interface of the Streams API represents a controller allowing control of a ReadableStream's state and internal queue. Byte stream controllers are for byte streams.
rbs-controller-class.title: ReadableByteStreamController

rbs-controller-close.summary: The close() method of the ReadableByteStreamController interface closes the associated stream.
rbs-controller-close.title: ReadableByteStreamController.close()

rbs-controller-constructor.summary: The ReadableByteStreamController() constructor creates and returns a ReadableByteStreamController() object instance.
rbs-controller-constructor.title: ReadableByteStreamController.ReadableByteStreamController()

rbs-controller-desired-size.summary: The desiredSize getter property of the ReadableByteStreamController interface returns the desired size required to fill the stream's internal queue.
rbs-controller-desired-size.title: ReadableByteStreamController.desiredSize

rbs-controller-enqueue.summary: The enqueue() method of the ReadableByteStreamController interface enqueues a given chunk in the associated stream.
rbs-controller-enqueue.title: ReadableByteStreamController.enqueue()

rbs-controller-error.summary: The error() method of the ReadableByteStreamController interface causes any future interactions with the associated stream to error.
rbs-controller-error.title: ReadableByteStreamController.error()

rs-byob-request-class.summary: The ReadableStreamBYOBRequest interface of the Streams API represents a pull request into a ReadableByteStreamController view.
rs-byob-request-class.title: ReadableStreamBYOBRequest

rs-byob-request-constructor.summary: The ReadableStreamBYOBRequest() constructor creates and returns a ReadableStreamBYOBRequest() object instance.
rs-byob-request-constructor.title: ReadableStreamBYOBRequest.ReadableStreamBYOBRequest()

rs-byob-request-respond.summary: The error() method of the ReadableStreamBYOBRequest interface xxx
rs-byob-request-respond.title: ReadableStreamBYOBRequest.respond()

rs-byob-request-respond-with-new-view.summary: The respondWithNewView() method of the ReadableStreamBYOBRequest interface xxx
rs-byob-request-respond-with-new-view.title: ReadableStreamBYOBRequest.respondWithNewView()

rs-byob-request-view.summary: The view getter property of the ReadableStreamBYOBRequest interface returns the current view.
rs-byob-request-view.title: ReadableStreamBYOBRequest.view

rs-cancel.summary: The cancel() method of the ReadableStream interface cancels the associated stream. The supplied reason parameter will be given to the underlying source, which may or may not use it.
rs-cancel.title: ReadableStream.cancel()

rs-class.summary: The ReadableStream interface of the Streams API represents a readable stream of byte data. The Fetch API offers a concrete instance of a ReadableStream through the body property of a Response object.
rs-class.title: ReadableStream

rs-constructor.summary: The ReadableStream() constructor creates and returns a readable stream object from the given handlers.
rs-constructor.title: ReadableStream.ReadableStream()

rs-default-controller-class.summary: The ReadableStreamDefaultController interface of the Streams API represents a controller allowing control of a ReadableStream's state and internal queue. Default controllers are for streams that are not byte streams.

firefox.notes: Not yet enabled by default. See bug 1389628.

firefox_android.notes: Not yet enabled by default. See bug 1389628.

rs-default-controller-class.title: ReadableStreamDefaultController

rs-default-controller-close.summary: The close() method of the ReadableStreamDefaultController interface closes the associated stream.
rs-default-controller-close.title: ReadableStreamDefaultController.close()

rs-default-controller-constructor.summary: The ReadableStreamDefaultController() constructor creates and returns a ReadableStreamDefaultController() object instance.
rs-default-controller-constructor.title: ReadableStreamDefaultController.ReadableStreamDefaultController()

rs-default-controller-desired-size.summary: The desiredSize getter property of the ReadableStreamDefaultController interface returns the desired size required to fill the stream's internal queue.
rs-default-controller-desired-size.title: ReadableStreamDefaultController.desiredSize

rs-default-controller-enqueue.summary: The enqueue() method of the ReadableStreamDefaultController interface enqueues a given chunk in the associated stream.
rs-default-controller-enqueue.title: ReadableStreamDefaultController.enqueue()

rs-default-controller-error.summary: The error() method of the ReadableStreamDefaultController interface causes any future interactions with the associated stream to error.
rs-default-controller-error.title: ReadableStreamDefaultController.error()

rs-get-reader.summary: The getReader() method of the ReadableStream interface creates a reader and locks the stream to it. While the stream is locked, no other reader can be acquired until this one is released.
rs-get-reader.title: ReadableStream.getReader()

rs-locked.summary: The locked getter property of the ReadableStream interface returns whether or not the readable stream is locked to a reader.
rs-locked.title: ReadableStream.locked

rs-pipe-through.summary: The pipeThrough() method of the ReadableStream interface provides a chainable way of piping the current stream through a transform stream or any other writable/readable pair.
rs-pipe-through.title: ReadableStream.pipeThrough()

rs-pipe-to.summary: The pipeTo() method of the ReadableStream interface pipes the current ReadableStream to a given WritableStream and returns a promise that fulfills when the piping process completes successfully, or rejects if any errors were encountered.
rs-pipe-to.title: ReadableStream.pipeTo()

rs-tee.summary: The tee() method of the ReadableStream interface tees the current readable stream, returning a two-element array containing the two resulting branches as new ReadableStream instances.
rs-tee.title: ReadableStream.tee()

ws-abort.summary: The abort() method of the WritableStream interface aborts the stream, signaling that the producer can no longer successfully write to the stream and it is to be immediately moved to an error state, with any queued writes discarded.
ws-abort.title: WritableStream.abort()

ws-class.summary: The WritableStream interface of the the Streams API provides a standard abstraction for writing streaming data to a destination, known as a sink. This object comes with built-in backpressure and queuing.
ws-class.title: WritableStream

ws-constructor.summary: The WritableStream() constructor creates a new WritableStream object instance.
ws-constructor.title: WritableStream.WritableStream()

ws-default-controller-class.summary: The WritableStreamDefaultController interface of the the Streams API represents a controller allowing control of a WritableStream's state. When constructing a WritableStream, the underlying sink is given a corresponding WritableStreamDefaultController instance to manipulate.
ws-default-controller-class.title: WritableStreamDefaultController

ws-default-controller-constructor.summary: The WritableStreamDefaultController() constructor creates and returns a WritableStreamDefaultController() object instance.
ws-default-controller-constructor.title: WritableStreamDefaultController.WritableStreamDefaultController()

ws-default-controller-error.summary: The error() method of the WritableStreamDefaultController interface causes any future interactions with the associated stream to error.
ws-default-controller-error.title: WritableStreamDefaultController.error()

ws-get-writer.summary: The getWriter() method of the WritableStream interface returns a new instance of WritableStreamDefaultWriter and locks the stream to that instance. While the stream is locked, no other writer can be acquired until this one is released.
ws-get-writer.title: WritableStream.getWriter()

ws-locked.summary: The locked getter property of the WritableStream interface returns a boolean indicating whether the WritableStream is locked to a writer.
ws-locked.title: WritableStream.locked
